{"Body": "TRENTON, Mich. (AP) â€” Authorities say an 18-year-old man who attacked officers with a lawnmower blade has died after being shot by police.\n\nThe shooting happened around 4:30 p.m. Thursday at a home in Trenton.\n\nPolice say they responded to reports of a young man who was highly agitated and, after officers arrived at the home, the man attacked them with the blade.\n\nPolice say they first tried to subdue the man with a stun gun before the shooting. State police say he was taken to a hospital, where he died Friday morning. His name wasn't immediately released.\n\nAn injured officer had a cut hand and was treated before being released from the hospital. The attack and shooting are under investigation by state police.", "Title": "Police kill man attacking officers with lawnmower blade - DailyPress.net | News, Sports, Jobs, Escanaba Information | The Daily Press"}